{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f69cb283-03d0-4cfb-8268-ba2b61efccbf","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n### 1. Update packages\n- **Upgrade** `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it adds Microsoft.Testing.Platform support).\n- **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's the VSTest entry point and is no longer needed.\n\n### 2. Enable the new platform\nAdd this to your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 3. Run tests\n- Use `dotnet test` as before — it works with the new platform.\n- You can also run the test project directly (`dotnet run`) since it now produces an executable.\n\n### Key notes\n- NUnit3TestAdapter **v5+** dropped VSTest support entirely, so it's a one-way migration.\n- If you rely on `.runsettings`, most settings carry over but review the [Microsoft.Testing.Platform docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform) for any differences.\n- Extensions like code coverage or TRX reporting need their Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents (e.g., `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c8d62659-253b-4664-804f-b37c4b55ab4f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":393,"requestId":"A02C:2D289A:C15A94:E16999:69FE855B"},"id":"e0282eab-715c-48c7-a6a2-d88c270524c2","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:52:54.063Z","parentId":"0135bb9f-0ef8-450e-b082-339f8d9e789b"}
